latestIgtvVideos.caption: 48 billion. That’s how many bees have been required to pollinate California’s almonds in recent years. It’s no secret that KIND 💛s almonds. That’s why, by the end of 2022, 51% of our almond supply will be sourced from bee-friendly farmland, and 100% by 2025. 🐝 To learn more, click the link in our bio (kindsnacks.com/bees)

#pridemonth may be over, but we’re here to celebrate all year long 🎉 We began our partnership with @aliforneycenter in 2018 with the launch of our Snack & Give Back program, a multi-year program to inspire kindness and empathy. The Ali Forney Center is the nation’s largest organization dedicated to supporting homeless LGBTQ+ youth. This year, KIND has donated $125,000 to the Ali Forney Center, with $25,000 specifically being used to support LGBTQ+ youth in Florida.

The KIND ‘Better Than Ice Cream’ Truck is on the way, Bentonville! You’ll be able to find us at the @bfffestival from 4PM - 10PM. Stop by to try our KIND FROZEN® Treat Bars – on us — this weekend! 👀 #KINDFrozen #LIVEKIND
The next stop on our summer tour: Montauk, NY! Come try our KIND Frozen® Bars (on us!) at the KIND ‘Better Than Ice Cream’ Truck. Tag your friends headed to the ☀️🌊🏖 this weekend!

Head to @kindsnacks on TikTok to join us for our #WorldBeeDay party! 🐝 Give us a follow to bee alerted when the #beedaybash starts on 5/20 at 5pm PT/7 pm CT. #kindpartner @mr.mrs.beerescue will bee there, and you’re invited, too. #beetok
